📊 Types of Charts Used in the Dashboard

1️⃣ KPI Cards

Used for summary metrics.

Examples:

•	Total Listings

•	Total Reviews

•	Average Price

•	Average Review Score

Power BI Visual:

Card Visual

________________________________________
2️⃣ Clustered Column Chart

Used in:

Price Range Booking Distribution

Price buckets like:

•	0–100

•	100–200

•	200–300

•	etc.

Chart Type:

Clustered Column Chart

________________________________________
3️⃣ Donut Chart

Used for Accommodation Type Distribution

Categories:

•	Entire place

•	Private room

•	Hotel room

•	Shared room

Chart Type:

Donut Chart

________________________________________
4️⃣ Ranking Bar Chart (City Ratings)

Used in the Rating Category page to compare cities.

Cities:

•	Mexico City

•	Rio de Janeiro

•	Cape Town

•	New York

•	etc.

Chart Type:

Clustered Column Chart

________________________________________
5️⃣ Seasonal Booking Chart

Used in the Season Analysis page.

Cities vs booking counts.

Chart Type:

Clustered Column Chart

________________________________________
6️⃣ Slicers

Used for filtering data dynamically.

Examples:

•	Month slicer

•	Year slicer

•	Rating category slicer

Power BI Visual:

Slicer

________________________________________
7️⃣ Navigation Buttons

Left sidebar navigation:

•	Overview

•	Season Analysis

•	Rating Category

•	Key Pointers

Power BI Visual:

Buttons with Page Navigation

